                    <span>I was recently diagnosed with Type II Diabetes, after being overweight and eating too much sugar for years.  This was a devastating blow to me, emotionally and physically.  <p>My doctor actually suggested I pick up a copy of Eric Harr's book -- to work my way slowly back to exercise. I began with the basic, Level I program in the book and it was a nice, gradual process.  I am feeling so good these days.  My doctor says my "good cholesterol" is up and "bad" is down.  I've lost 14 pounds and I am aiming for my first triathlon in 3 weeks.<p>I feel like Eric Harr's book has saved my life, because I used to hate exercise and I always ate poorly. Now, I'm on a new track because of this book.  I can feel myself LIVING again.<p>If you want to change your life -- and have fun learning how to be healthy again -- buy this book. It is a lifesaver.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Great Book!</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
